{
  "sn2.7:0.1": "Linked Discourses 2 ",
  "sn2.7:0.2": "Chapter One ",
  "sn2.7:0.3": "7. With Pañcālacaṇḍa ",
  "sn2.7:1.1": "At Sāvatthī. ",
  "sn2.7:1.2": "Standing to one side, the god Pañcālacaṇḍa recited this verse in the Buddha’s presence: ",
  "sn2.7:2.1": "“The opening amid confinement ",
  "sn2.7:2.2": "was discovered by the Buddha of vast intelligence, ",
  "sn2.7:2.3": "who woke up to absorption, ",
  "sn2.7:2.4": "the sage, the solitary bull.” ",
  "sn2.7:3.1": "“Even amid confinement they discover,” ",
  "sn2.7:3.2": "said the Buddha to Pañcālacaṇḍa, ",
  "sn2.7:3.3": "“the principle for attaining extinguishment. ",
  "sn2.7:3.4": "Those who have acquired mindfulness ",
  "sn2.7:3.5": "are perfectly serene in samādhi.”"
}